v:4 c:$ m:T02-wire-pencil-pointer role:dev x:typescript/vue3
gate: LOCKED

task: Make Pencil and Pointer tools behave differently in the canvas, and wire PianoRollView buttons to setTool

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/piano-roll.ts
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/components/PianoRollView.vue

depends: [T01-pianoroll-tool-api]

context: |
  Semantics for this audio-jam piano roll:
    - PENCIL  = current behaviour: mousedown/drag plays notes live (the
                instrument you hear). This is the "perform" tool.
    - POINTER = passive/select: hovering/clicking the grid does NOT trigger
                audio. Used to inspect without making sound. (Cursor changes,
                no triggerNote.)

steps (piano-roll.ts):
  1. In setupCanvasEvents() mousedown handler: early-return WITHOUT triggerNote
     when this.tool === 'pointer' (still allow note read for future hover, but
     no audio, no this.mouseDown = true).
  2. In mousemove handler: already guarded by this.mouseDown, so pointer mode
     (which never sets mouseDown) is inert — verify no triggerNote fires.
  3. Set canvas cursor to reflect tool: in setTool(), update
     this.gridCanvas.style.cursor = tool === 'pencil' ? 'crosshair' : 'default'.

steps (PianoRollView.vue):
  4. activeTool ref already exists (L60). In its @click handlers (L75, L89),
     after setting activeTool, call pianoRoll?.setTool(activeTool.value).
     Cleanest: replace the inline `activeTool = 'x'` with a selectTool('x')
     method that sets the ref AND calls pianoRoll.setTool.
  5. On mount (after pianoRoll created, ~L35), call pianoRoll.setTool(activeTool.value)
     so the initial 'pencil' cursor is applied.

done:
  - Pencil tool: click/drag on grid plays notes (unchanged behaviour) + crosshair cursor
  - Pointer tool: click/drag on grid produces NO audio + default cursor
  - Toolbar active-state highlight still tracks activeTool
  - tsc --noEmit passes; manual: switch tools, confirm audio only in pencil
